Exposure pathway. [adapted from EEA Glossary and EPA; and project meetings].
The course a substance takes from its source to the exposed individual or population, or a part of that course. An exposure pathway involves in general one or several transfer mechanisms from emission sources to exposure sources, and/or between several related exposure sources (.e.g. from soil to food).
